# Personal Portfolio Development Rules

## Project Context
- React-based portfolio for software engineer & mountain athlete
- Focus on clean, responsive design with mountain/outdoor aesthetic
- Sections: About, Projects, Experience, Tools, Blog
- Target audience: potential employers, collaborators, outdoor community

## Code Standards
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Implement responsive design (mobile-first)
- Follow React best practices (hooks, functional components)
- Use CSS modules or styled-components for styling
- Include accessibility features (ARIA labels, semantic HTML)

## Design Preferences
- Mountain/outdoor color palette (earth tones, forest greens, snow whites)
- Clean, modern typography
- Smooth animations and transitions
- High-contrast ratios for readability
- Fast loading times and performance optimization

## Mountain Athlete Theme Integration
- Incorporate outdoor imagery and metaphors
- Use terminology that bridges tech and athletics
- Highlight transferable skills (endurance, problem-solving, goal achievement)
- Include adventure/gear-related projects if applicable

## Technical Stack Preferences
- React + TypeScript
- CSS-in-JS or CSS Modules
- React Router for navigation
- Framer Motion for animations
- Responsive design with CSS Grid/Flexbox
- Performance optimization (lazy loading, code splitting)